 0054:     """
 0055:     An atom group. This class is based on the :class:`Atom` class, except that
 0056:     it uses :ref:`atom types <atom-types>` instead of elements, and all
 0057:     attributes are lists rather than individual values. The attributes are:
 0058: 
 0059:     =================== =================== ====================================
 0060:     Attribute           Type                Description
 0061:     =================== =================== ====================================
 0062:     `atomType`          ``list``            The allowed atom types (as :class:`AtomType` objects)
 0063:     `radicalElectrons`  ``list``            The allowed numbers of radical electrons (as short integers)
 0064:     `charge`            ``list``            The allowed formal charges (as short integers)
 0065:     `label`             ``str``             A string label that can be used to tag individual atoms
 0066:     `lonePairs`         ``list``            The number of lone electron pairs
 0067:     =================== =================== ====================================
 0068: 
 0069:     Each list represents a logical OR construct, i.e. an atom will match the
 0070:     group if it matches *any* item in the list. However, the
 0071:     `radicalElectrons`, and `charge` attributes are linked
 0072:     such that an atom must match values from the same index in each of these in
 0073:     order to match.
 0074:     """
 0075:
